Yvette Andréyor https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yvette_Andr%C3%A9yor 0 Yvette Andréyor (6 August 1891 – 30 October 1962) was a French actress most popular in the era of silent film. She appeared in 108 films between 1910 and 1962. She was born and died in Paris, France.
